```json
{
  "application": "MPI",
  "details": {
    "software": {
      "openmpi": "4.1.1"
    },
    "resources": {
      "partition": "amdrome",
      "node": "amd1",
      "nodes": 1,
      "tasks": 2,
      "gpus_per_node": 2,
      "cpus_per_task": 64,
      "gpus_per_task": 1,
      "time": "00:10:00",
      "output_file": "./stdout_%J",
      "error_file": "./stderr_%J"
    }
  }
}
```

This script uses the **MPI** (Message Passing Interface) library for parallel computing. The script utilizes the OpenMPI version 4.1.1 and runs on a specific node (amd1) within the amdrome partition of a cluster. It requires 2 nodes, each with 2 GPUs and allocates 64 CPUs per task and 1 GPU per task. The job runs for a maximum of 10 minutes and logs its output and errors to separate files.
